race.comment: JAHANGIR (7) resumed in good order at Sale, finishing 1.3L away on a heavy deck over this trip. Getting onto a firmer deck today is a big tick for him and he continues to show some class. Can build on the fresh effort and go one better today. IMMINANCE (10) can mix his form a touch, though she will appreciate the sting out of the ground today. She was just outclassed on the Heath at Caulfield last time out and getting back to a race of this calibre is a big tick. Can bounce back. SPEIR (3) has impressed in his jumpouts coming into this and the claim of Kennedy is a big tick. Should get his chance from the draw. BOLD PRINT (6) wasn't beaten fat last start at Cranbourne and has claims.
